{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, Conditional Analogy Generative Adversarial Network (CAGAN) (Kips et al. 2020) is the first method to introduce the cycle-consistent in the virtual try-on task to solve the problem that paired images are difficult to obtain.",
    "CAGAN exhibits the capability to implicitly acquire segmentation masks, eliminating the need for costly and time-consuming supervised labeled data.",
    "CAGAN also demonstrates its ability to directly predict images that possess the desired attributes, streamlining the process and bypassing the requirement for explicit segmentation information.",
    "Furthermore, Ge et al. (2021a) introduced the Disentangled Cycle-Consistency Try-On Network (DCTON) as an improvement upon CAGAN.",
    "DCTON generates highly realistic try-on images by effectively distinguishing clothing regions from non-clothing regions."
  ]
}